Lisa Marie Presley, singer-songwriter and the only child of Elvis Presley, has died aged 54. Presley died on Thursday after being hospitalised due to a suspected cardiac arrest. She had attended the 2023 Golden Globe Awards, with her mother Priscilla Presley, just two days earlier to support Baz Luhrmann’s biopic Elvis. Following her father’s career path, Lisa Marie Presley released three albums during her lifetime, keeping her famous surname in the spotlight. From her early days at Graceland to her marriage with Michael Jackson and beyond, here is a look back at the life of Lisa Marie Presley in pictures. [ Lisa Marie Presley, the daughter of Elvis, dies at 54 ] [ ‘I was trying not to refer right off the bat to my heritage’: Lisa Marie Presley on Elvis, Michael Jackson and her music ]